args: Looks like we made it in time!\nAre you two okay?!
We'll save the explanations for later.\nFirst, we're gonna defeat the cause\nof all these nightmares!
Defeated at last. Everyone's dreams\nshould be peaceful once more.
Sorry for worrying all of you.
I'm just glad you're both all right.
But how did you all get here?\nYou are adults—you shouldn't\nhave the power to dream freely.
We had a little help from the kids—\njust like the two of you did.
They all wished for Notte to be okay,\nwhich is how we were able to help.
You all did that for little ol' me?
I'm glad you're in one piece, Peony,\nbut runnin' off alone like that is a\ngood way to get yourself hurt.
If we hadn't gotten here when we did...
I'm sorry. When I thought Notte was in\ndanger, I just couldn't sit still.
I guess that's proof of how much\nyou care for her.
Aw, thanks, Peony. But still, I...
The fiend is defeated, and yet your dream\nremains dark. Is there something you are\nstill worried about?
...I'm mad that I made you feel lonely.
I'm sorry! I totally wasn't trying to be a\nbig snoopypants, but I heard what you\nsaid to Pipple about being lonely.
And about how we forget our dreams and\nall the time we spend with you there.
And yet, you're always so bright\nand cheery whenever we wake up.\nI can't imagine how hard that must be.
You're my FRIEND, man, and I hurt you\nevery single night. I just...I don't even\nknow how to begin dealing with that.

Dreams simply are what they are—
don't hold their nature against them.
Don't let bad dreams like this one make
you unhappy.
To me, that would be the saddest\nand loneliest thing of all—your\nsweet dreams are all I require.
So you don't MIND if we forget you\nso long as we have good dreams?
The dreams of mortals are what\ngive life to us ljósálfar.
We want everyone to dream—\nhappy ones, if possible.
And yes, I know you will forget most of\nwhat happens in the world of dreams...
But that doesn't mean we aren't\nstill friends when you wake up.
That friendship makes me very happy;\nit is more than enough.
Ah, now THIS is the kind of dream I like.\nIt's so bright and warm and...happy.
And with that, I think it is time for us to\nwake. Let's all go nighty-night!
